Areva, Vallourec Shares May Move: French Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A n n e   S w a r d s o n   a n d   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 
2011-05-24T04:00:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/areva-vallourec-shares-may-move-french-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Paris. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices are
from the last close.  France’s benchmark  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  fell 2.1 percent to
3,906.98, while the broader  SBF 120 Index (SBF120)  dropped 2 percent to
2,947.62.  Areva SA (CEI)  : The world’s largest maker of nuclear
reactors purchased the remaining stake in Areva Koblitz, buying
the 30 percent of the Brazilian power-generation supplier it
didn’t already own. The shares fell 1.2 percent to 30.25 euros.  Vallourec SA (VK)  : The producer of steel pipes said it
would acquire Saudi Seamless Pipes Factory Co., or Zamil Pipes,
in Saudi Arabia for $135 million. The shares fell 1.1 percent to
85.99 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Anne Swardson in Paris at 
 aswardson@bloomberg.net ;
Fabio Benedetti-Valentini in Paris at 
 fabiobv@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root in Paris at   vroot@bloomberg.net  